{{Han compound|心|青|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=heart|tr=*dzeŋ|tr2=*tsʰˤeŋ}}.

===Etymology===
Its meaning "feeling" prompts {{zh-ref|Benedict (1976)}} to connect it to {{cog|sit-pro|*s/k-niŋ|*s-niŋ|heart; brain; mind}}; while its other meaning "proper nature, situation" suggests cognacy to {{zh-l|生|to live, life}} ({{zh-ref|Boltz, 1976}}), though the initials of {{och-l|情|tr=*dzeŋ}} vs. {{och-l|生|tr=*srêŋ}} are difficult to reconcile ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}) – not withstanding {{zh-ref|Zhengzhang (2003)}}'s reconstructions {{och-l|情}} vs. {{och-l|生|id=1}}.

{{och-l|情|tr=*dzeŋ}} may be compared with {{och-l|靜|tr=*dzeŋ;dzeŋh}} and {{och-l|靖|tr=*dzeŋʔ}} (“still; settled; at peace”), as well as {{och-l|清|tr=*tsʰeŋ}} and {{och-l|淨|tr=*dzeŋh;dzˤreŋ}} (“clear; clean; unobscured”), perhaps reflecting a semantic field of clarity, settledness, and the manifestation of an actual or inherent state.

